    "narrative": "Our primary objective for today\u2019s slate centers on **Kyle Tucker** (76.90) and **Jackson Merrill** (74.69), who represent our highest-ceiling plays against favorable pitching matchups. **Kyle Tucker** benefits from a strong wind-out factor and consistent contact metrics (xwOBA 0.372) against Alcantara, while **Jackson Merrill** occupies the leadoff spot against Taillon, leveraging a significant +13% platoon boost to maximize his production. Similarly, **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (72.43) and **Josh Lowe** (72.21) offer high-floor outcomes. **Josh Lowe** is particularly notable; despite the park downgrade, his 19% boost from Fedde\u2019s projected struggles and a 93% efficiency rating regarding stolen base opportunities make him an essential start given our desperate need for speed.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench was **Miguel Vargas** (58.56). He flirted with a starting spot, but ultimately lost out to the superior platoon and order-based efficiency of **Liam Hicks** (51.47) and **Nasim Nunez** (50.48), whose situational advantages\u2014namely **Liam Hicks**\u2019s wind-aided outlook and the necessity of keeping high-speed options active\u2014tipped the scale. While **Miguel Vargas** remains a solid depth piece, he did not clear the 60-point threshold required to displace our core starters in this specific matchup configuration.\n\nFinally, we must monitor the environment closely. **Drake Baldwin** faces a significant hurdle in the form of Skubal\u2019s 2.71 xERA; his sub-50 score (47.27) suggests he is merely a \"marginal\" play, and we are rostering him primarily out of necessity given the lack of alternatives. Most critically, our roster is reeling from the loss of **Gunnar Henderson**, whose game was postponed today, and **Jordan Westburg**, who remains sidelined on the IL. With no active production from those slots, we must rely on the calculated platoon advantages of **Andy Pages** and **Marcell Ozuna** to carry our offensive output through the evening.",
